Tips to start(all the keys)
1. You should set the o!m speed to 20-25 (fixed), with that, you'll learn 2 things.
1.1. You will learn to hand hard patterns faster, because your vision will be better than before and you will see the notes really well.
1.2. You'll improve faster in general (accuracy, fingerspeed,...).
2. Start playing standard converted maps after you reach an A really close to a S in 2,00 stars songs, because:
2.1. Because the standard converted maps, there are mainly mapped with LNs (Large Notes, Sliders in standard), and a lot of people scores a green 300 and not a 300 rainbow.
2.2. In the standard maps, apart from the LNs, the double notes and triple notes are really common (the mania 2,00 star maps, rarely have a dobule note or a triple note).
3. Try to start playing 7K. Because:
3.3. You will use more fingers there and automatically, you'll learn to play the other keys.
3.4. If you play the other keys, you're limiting your potential using less keys, and if you want to start playing other keys, It'll be harder.
4. Try to listen your keyboard when you tap the key at the same time. Why?
4.1. You'll learn how fast you need to tap the BPM pattern (jumpstream, stream, deathstream, jackhammer, whatever) because you're listening the keyboard and listening how speed do you tap de keys.
5. Check this thread.
Mods/GD
I can mod your map or I could do a 4K (Only 4K) GD if you want, but the song should have this.
- My GD should be in a Speedcore (Renard TQBF, etc) map, or just a really high BPM with a really fast rythm (240-360BPM).
- I mainly mod 4K, but I could try 7K. And as I said before with the GDs, those are the same reasons for the mod too.
- If I like the song, I would do a Insane GD (4,30stars to 6 NOT OVERMAPPED).

4/7K: [url=https://www.dropbox.com/sh/j0egng2zcb2b5hn/AAAOfbzOA7SOCFuqOwSvl_0_a?dl=0]Convert[/url] by [url=https://osu.ppy.sh/u/4056690]Todestrieb[/url] (This pack contains random BMS and Stepmania converts songs)[/box]

[box=Tips to start(all the keys)][size=150]1.[/size] You should set the o!m speed to 20-25 (fixed), with that, you'll learn 2 things.
       [b] 1.1.[/b] You will learn to hand hard patterns faster, because your vision will be better than before and you will see the notes really well.
        [b]1.2.[/b] You'll improve faster in general (accuracy, fingerspeed,...).
[size=150]2.[/size] Start playing standard converted maps after you reach an A really close to a S in 2,00 stars songs, because:
      [b]  2.1.[/b] Because the standard converted maps, there are mainly mapped with LNs (Large Notes, Sliders in standard), and a lot of people scores a green 300 and not a 300 rainbow.
      [b] 2.2.[/b] In the standard maps, apart from the LNs, the double notes and triple notes are really common (the mania 2,00 star maps, rarely have a dobule note or a triple note). 
[size=150]3. [/size]Try to start playing 7K. Because:
      [b] 3.3.[/b] You will use more fingers there and automatically, you'll learn to play the other keys.
     [b]  3.4.[/b] If you play the other keys, you're limiting your potential using less keys, and if you want to start playing other keys, It'll be harder.
[size=150]4.[/size] Try to listen your keyboard when you tap the key at the same time. Why?
[b]4.1.[/b] You'll learn how fast you need to tap the BPM pattern (jumpstream, stream, deathstream, jackhammer, whatever) because you're listening the keyboard and listening how speed do you tap de keys.
[size=150]5.[/size] [url=https://osu.ppy.sh/forum/t/146615]Check this thread.[/url][/box]
[box=Mods/GD]I can mod your map or I could do a 4K (Only 4K) GD if you want, but the song should have this.
- My GD should be in a Speedcore (Renard TQBF, etc) map, or just a really high BPM with a really fast rythm (240-360BPM).
- I mainly mod 4K, but I could try 7K. And as I said before with the GDs, those are the same reasons for the mod too.
- If I like the song, I would do a Insane GD (4,30stars to 6 [b][u]NOT OVERMAPPED[/u][/b]).[/box]
